{"build_type":"executable","description":"LLM reader op.map: read an IPM package (JSON) from stdin and emit a compact bodyless skeleton {package, functions:[{name,arity,ninstr,calls}], confidence, omitted, hash} to stdout — a cheap structural map so an agent can orient before drilling into one function, instead of reading the whole file. Guards malformed input (non-JSON, missing function_definitions/package_name) with a structured error object rather than crashing (§7). Shares the envelope tail (confidence/omitted/hash) via finalize_reader_response_envelope and the content hash via compute_content_hash_of_cstring. Parses with json-tree-node, read_all_of_stdin, summarize_function_members_into_skeleton.","module_name":"generate-package-skeleton-towards-agent-retrieval","package_name":"generate-package-skeleton-towards-agent-retrieval","function_definitions":{"generate-package-skeleton-towards-agent-retrieval":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_fd","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"function_definitions"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_pkgname","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"package_name"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_package","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"package"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_functions","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"functions"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_total","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":